imes that texture can point the wrong way entirely.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Upgrade the midnight watchlist from \u201cstrong tape observed\u201d to \u201cstrong but unstable tape observed.\u201d\n- Keep 00h out of live hours.\n- Preserve PM copy flow as a secondary crowd-state feature, not a directional confirmation tool.\n\n**Next:** On future midnight sessions, explicitly track **direction changes within the session** in addition to bias strength and off-midpoint duration. If 00h keeps flipping direction despite high bias, that becomes a reason to keep it excluded even if it looks active.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-22 00:29 UTC \u2014 [P3: Strategy Development] V7c Midnight Watchlist Spec Written\n\n**Task:** Convert the new midnight evidence into a disciplined implementation path so 00h does not stay an abstract debate or turn into an impulsive live expansion.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains flat outside active hours.\n- I wrote a shadow-only spec at `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v7c-midnight-watchlist.spec.md`.\n- The spec keeps 00h excluded from live trading but formalizes w",
